		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> <date>5 Sepr 1865</date><add>&#63;</add></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I send you<lb/> a paper called the Christian Advocate<lb/> containing some remarks on the<lb/> late dedication of a &#8220;progressive<lb/> Jewish Temple&#8221; in this city.  Should<lb/> you deem those reflections worthy<lb/> of any notice in your publication I<lb/> have to request that you will not<lb/> in any way intimate that you recd<lb/> the paper from a correspondent or<lb/> any thing of that kind&#44; because it<lb/> is considered here now a <sic>henious</sic> of<lb/>fence to do aught which may in any<lb/> way reflect on Reform or Reformers&#44;<lb/> and as I am marked&#44; I do not desire<lb/> to be publicly mixed with their</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>affair&#8212;Hashictures<add>&#63;</add> are how<lb/>&#61;ever correct &#38; true to the letter&#44; the<lb/> denial by both the Revd professors<lb/> of all that we have been taught<lb/> as constituting Judaism&#44; was com<lb/>plete &#38; emphatic&#8212;Rationalism<lb/> is to govern&#44; against the words of<lb/> inspiration&#8212;Miracles such as<lb/> the <placeName>red sea</placeName> dividing to permit the cross<lb/>ing of <placeName>Judeas</placeName> <add>&#63;</add>&#44; are also mere follies&#44;<lb/> restoration to <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName> &#38; the coming<lb/> of a redeemer to <placeName>Israel</placeName> only old fogy<lb/> notions&#8212;and all the landmarks of<lb/> our faith entirely gone&#8212;and not<lb/> to side with these tenets is to<lb/> be ostracised&#58; for <hi rend="underline">all</hi> the people<lb/> are led away nearly by heresies<lb/> of the day.  I wish you all the<lb/> complements of the season that you<lb/> may be inscribed in the book of life<lb/> &#38; that the coming year may be a<lb/> year of joy &#38; happiness to you &#38; that<lb/> your labors in the vineyard<lb/> may bring forth abundant &#38; good fruits&#8212;I <del>wish</del> send<lb/> &#36;10 herein as I know I must be in<lb/>debted to you I do not wish you<lb/> to acknowledge receipt in your<lb/> paper as I shall then be pointed<lb/> out &#38; I candidly tell you that<lb/> for policy sake I am compelled to<lb/> be at least or seem passive&#44; tho&#39;<lb/> I never disguise my disgust &#38; abhor<lb/>&#61;ence of the schemes of those who<lb/> call themselves here teachers in<lb/> <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#8212;  With regards I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)">truly yrs</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Joseph Abraham Esq</persName><add>&#63;</add></p>
		</body>
